Perendale
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a sheep bred for wool and meat.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: breed of sheep named after Sir Geoffrey Sylvester Peren, 1892-1980. Palmerston North sheep breeder and one of the founders of Massey University.
